  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nKey legal elements often include:\n- Knowingly disguising proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legitimate\n- Transferring or converting assets to conceal their origin\n- Intentionally participating in financial transactions to hide illegal funds\n\nDifferent countries have variations in precise legal definitions and specific penalties.\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed information about money laundering laws in a specific jurisdiction?",
